# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration - Already Implemented

## Summary
Vercel Web Analytics is **already properly installed and configured** in this Next.js App Router project.

## Current Implementation Status

### 1. Package Installation ✓
- **Package**: `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1
- **Status**: Already installed in package.json dependencies
- **Verification**: Confirmed via `npm list @vercel/analytics`

### 2. Analytics Component Integration ✓
- **Location**: `site/app/layout.tsx` (root layout file)
- **Implementation**: 
  ```typescript
  import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";
  
  export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
    return (
      <html lang="en">
        <body>
          {children}
          <Analytics />
        </body>
      </html>
    );
  }
  ```
- **Status**: Correctly placed at the end of the body tag as per official Vercel documentation
- **Framework**: Next.js App Router (detected and verified)

### 3. Documentation Compliance ✓
Fetched latest documentation from: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

The current implementation follows the official Vercel documentation exactly:
- Uses correct import path: `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Component is placed in the root layout file
- Positioned at the end of the body element
- No additional configuration required for basic setup

### 4. Build Verification ✓
- **Build Status**: Successful ✓
- **Command**: `npm run build`
- **Result**: All pages compiled and generated successfully with no errors
- **Output**: 8/8 static pages generated successfully

